## Context

- Completed full Phase 1-5 analyst review of NF1-loss pan-cancer dependency atlas
- Reports saved to output/cancer/nf1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas/analysis/
- Success criteria: 0/4 fully met, 2/4 partially met. Genome-wide screen largely negative (1 hit at FDR<0.1: RIT1)
- Key positive finding: non-canonical MAPK dependency pattern (SHP2/GRB2/SHOC2/SPRED1-2, NOT MEK/ERK)
- SHP2 and RAF1 are the only credibly druggable targets with CRISPR support
- Critical issue flagged: TP53 confounding (71.5% co-mutation) uncontrolled. Developer task #1335 created for TP53-stratified analysis
- Research director task #1342 created for review of analyst assessment and validation scope decision
- MPNST findings are noise (undruggable, biologically implausible); only SHP2 has direct DepMap evidence
- PRISM analysis uninformative (key drug classes absent from dataset)
- Artifact flags: KRTAP21-1, SPRR1A (lineage), USP9Y (sex), OR10T2 (noise)
- Next: awaiting research_director decision on validation scope and developer TP53 correction
